This occurs in build 20011206 as well.

This appears NOT to be a duplicate of our other property store problems.  I have 
moved a copy of his workspace to 
dav/teams/core/downloads/bug_related_workspace/6673/

The workspace's root index store was corrupt.  It is impossible for me to debug 
how it got corrupted with only the given workspace to go by.  We'd need a 
reproducible case where the corruption ocurred.

However the error recovery code also had some bugs.  Our error recovery strategy 
here is to rename the property file and create a new property store.  This means 
that the user at worst loses their persistent properties, but won't continue to 
get error messages.  However, after failing to open it wasn't closing the 
underlying RandomAccessFile.  This means the file couldn't be renamed or 
deleted.  This meant that *every* subsequent attempt to access the root property 
file resulted in an error.

I have fixed up the error recovery code here, so it correctly renames the 
property file and recovers without annoying the user.

If we find no further information on how the corruption occurred, I'm going to  
close this bug.  Pat, if you have any leads on how your workbench got into this 
state, or if it happens again, let us know.  If you want to continue with that 
existing workspace, the workaround is to shutdown and delete the file 
workspace/.metadata/.plugins/org.eclipse.core.resources/.root/.properties

I can't even begin to imagine what might have happened. The only thing I can 
think of is that I was using the same workspace with various builds, including 
switching back to the 1.0 release for a little bit. Other than that, I don't 
know. I used the same workspace for a long time, so maybe a bug in one of the 
older builds somehow corrupted it.
Closing.  This problem hasn't been reproduced since last December.
